---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const docsContent = `
    <!-- ═══ GETTING STARTED ═══ -->
    <h1>Documentation</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Everything you need to add a glass-finished Gantt chart to your project. Install the package, pass your data, and let Emboss handle the design.</p>

    <h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="cm"># npm</span><br>npm install @emboss-js/core<br><br><span class="cm"># yarn</span><br>yarn add @emboss-js/core<br><br><span class="cm"># pnpm</span><br>pnpm add @emboss-js/core</div>
    <p>Emboss ships as a single package. Core rendering, free extensions, and paid bundles are all exported from <code>@emboss-js/core</code>. Paid features are gated by a runtime license key — without a key, paid extension code paths simply don't run. Free extensions and core rendering always work.</p>

    <h2 id="quick-start">Quick Start</h2>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="kw">import</span> { Emboss } <span class="kw">from</span> <span class="str">'@emboss-js/core'</span><br><span class="kw">import</span> <span class="str">'@emboss-js/core/themes/grayscale.css'</span><br><br><span class="kw">const</span> chart = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="fn">Emboss</span>(<span class="str">'#gantt'</span>, [<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;{ id: <span class="str">'1'</span>, type: <span class="str">'task'</span>, name: <span class="str">'Research'</span>,    start: <span class="num">0</span>,  duration: <span class="num">5</span>,  progress: <span class="num">100</span> },<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;{ id: <span class="str">'2'</span>, type: <span class="str">'task'</span>, name: <span class="str">'Design'</span>,      start: <span class="num">5</span>,  duration: <span class="num">8</span>,  progress: <span class="num">60</span>  },<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;{ id: <span class="str">'3'</span>, type: <span class="str">'task'</span>, name: <span class="str">'Development'</span>, start: <span class="num">13</span>, duration: <span class="num">15</span>, progress: <span class="num">0</span>   },<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;{ id: <span class="str">'4'</span>, type: <span class="str">'milestone'</span>, name: <span class="str">'Launch'</span>,  start: <span class="num">28</span>, duration: <span class="num">0</span>,  progress: <span class="num">0</span>   },<br>], { view: <span class="str">'week'</span> })</div>
    <p>That gives you glass-finished bars with grayscale styling, drag-to-reschedule, and a week view. Four rows, one import.</p>
    <p>Add free extensions for more features:</p>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="kw">import</span> { Emboss } <span class="kw">from</span> <span class="str">'@emboss-js/core'</span><br><span class="kw">import</span> { todayMarker, tooltips, dependencyArrows } <span class="kw">from</span> <span class="str">'@emboss-js/core/extensions/free'</span><br><br><span class="kw">const</span> chart = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="fn">Emboss</span>(<span class="str">'#gantt'</span>, tasks, {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;extensions: [<span class="fn">todayMarker</span>, <span class="fn">tooltips</span>, <span class="fn">dependencyArrows</span>],<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;theme: <span class="str">'dark'</span>,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;view: <span class="str">'week'</span><br>})</div>

    <h2 id="your-first-chart">Your First Chart</h2>
    <p>Every item in Emboss is a <code>Row</code>. The minimum fields you need to get a row on screen:</p>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="kw">const</span> rows = [<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;{<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;id: <span class="str">'1'</span>,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;type: <span class="str">'task'</span>,        <span class="cm">// 'task' | 'phase' | 'milestone' | 'subtask'</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;name: <span class="str">'Research'</span>,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;start: <span class="num">0</span>,           <span class="cm">// day offset from project start</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;duration: <span class="num">5</span>,        <span class="cm">// in days (0 for milestones)</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;progress: <span class="num">100</span>,      <span class="cm">// 0–100</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;depth: <span class="num">0</span>,           <span class="cm">// nesting level</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;parentId: <span class="kw">null</span>,     <span class="cm">// phase or task ID</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;collapsed: <span class="kw">false</span>,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;hidden: <span class="kw">false</span>,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;status: <span class="str">'done'</span>,     <span class="cm">// 'done' | 'active' | 'upcoming'</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;dependencies: []    <span class="cm">// IDs of rows this depends on</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;}<br>]</div>
    <p>Mount the chart on any container element. Emboss takes a CSS selector, your row data, and an optional config object:</p>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="kw">const</span> chart = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="fn">Emboss</span>(<span class="str">'#gantt'</span>, rows, {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;view: <span class="str">'week'</span>,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;theme: <span class="str">'grayscale'</span><br>})<br><br><span class="cm">// Listen for drag events</span><br>chart.<span class="fn">on</span>(<span class="str">'onDragEnd'</span>, (row, update) =&gt; {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;console.<span class="fn">log</span>(\`\${row.name} moved to day \${update.start}\`)<br>})</div>

    <!-- ═══ CORE CONCEPTS ═══ -->
    <h2 id="row-model">The Row Model</h2>
    <p>Everything in Emboss is a row. Phases, tasks, milestones, subtasks — one data structure, one render pipeline. The renderer receives an ordered array of Row objects and produces two synchronized outputs: a sidebar cell and a timeline cell for each row.</p>
    <p>This means:</p>
    <ul class="docs-list">
      <li>The sidebar and chart share <strong>one row index</strong>. Row 5 in the sidebar is row 5 on the timeline.</li>
      <li>Scroll position is synchronized by row index, not by separate scroll listeners.</li>
      <li>Hover state, selection state, and collapse state are properties of the row, not of the sidebar or chart independently.</li>
      <li>Extensions don't "add a sidebar" or "add milestones." They register renderers that handle specific row types.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The <code>Row</code> interface defines the shape of every item in your chart. Extensions enrich rows with additional fields (like <code>assignee</code>, <code>phaseColor</code>, <code>isCritical</code>) — the core type stays flat. Nobody creates parallel data structures.</p>

    <h2 id="state">State &amp; Mutation</h2>
    <p>One state object. One source of truth. All changes go through methods on the Emboss instance. Extensions read state, never write directly.</p>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="cm">// All state changes go through instance methods</span><br>chart.<span class="fn">setView</span>(<span class="str">'month'</span>)          <span class="cm">// recalculates scale, re-renders</span><br>chart.<span class="fn">setDensity</span>(<span class="str">'presentation'</span>) <span class="cm">// recalculates scale, re-renders</span><br>chart.<span class="fn">setTheme</span>(<span class="str">'dark'</span>)           <span class="cm">// swaps CSS class on root, re-renders</span><br>chart.<span class="fn">updateRow</span>(<span class="str">'task-1'</span>, {      <span class="cm">// merges changes into row</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;progress: <span class="num">80</span>,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;name: <span class="str">'Updated name'</span><br>})<br>chart.<span class="fn">toggleCollapse</span>(<span class="str">'phase-1'</span>)  <span class="cm">// expands/collapses children</span></div>
    <p>The <code>EmbossState</code> object contains the rows array, current view, density, theme, collapsed map, selected/hovered row IDs, settings, and the derived <code>Scale</code> object. Extensions hook into state changes via the event system.</p>

    <h2 id="views">Views &amp; Density</h2>
    <p>Four view modes control time scale. Three density options control row spacing. Each combination produces a specific scale — pixel-per-day, row height, bar height, and label size.</p>
    <div class="docs-code">chart.<span class="fn">setView</span>(<span class="str">'day'</span>)       <span class="cm">// day | week | month | quarter</span><br>chart.<span class="fn">setDensity</span>(<span class="str">'dense'</span>)  <span class="cm">// dense | working | presentation</span></div>
    <h3>Scale Values (view &times; density)</h3>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th></th><th>Day</th><th>Week</th><th>Month</th><th>Quarter</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Working</td><td>dw:44 rh:44 bh:26</td><td>dw:32 rh:44 bh:26</td><td>dw:12 rh:40 bh:22</td><td>dw:7 rh:40 bh:22</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Presentation</td><td>dw:48 rh:60 bh:34</td><td>dw:36 rh:60 bh:34</td><td>dw:14 rh:56 bh:30</td><td>dw:8 rh:56 bh:30</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Dense</td><td>dw:44 rh:30 bh:18</td><td>dw:32 rh:30 bh:18</td><td>dw:10 rh:28 bh:16</td><td>dw:5 rh:28 bh:16</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p><code>dw</code> = dayWidth (px/day), <code>rh</code> = rowHeight, <code>bh</code> = barHeight. Bar radius is half of barHeight. Label size ranges from 9.5px (dense/month) to 13px (presentation/day).</p>

    <h2 id="themes">Themes</h2>
    <p>Every visual value flows through <code>--emboss-</code> prefixed CSS custom properties. Swap a class on the container to change the entire feel. Grayscale and dark ship free. Vivid is included with the Organize bundle.</p>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="cm">// Grayscale (default)</span><br><span class="kw">import</span> <span class="str">'@emboss-js/core/themes/grayscale.css'</span><br><br><span class="cm">// Dark</span><br><span class="kw">import</span> <span class="str">'@emboss-js/core/themes/dark.css'</span><br>chart.<span class="fn">setTheme</span>(<span class="str">'dark'</span>)<br><br><span class="cm">// Vivid (requires Organize license)</span><br><span class="kw">import</span> <span class="str">'@emboss-js/core/extensions/organize/vivid.css'</span><br>chart.<span class="fn">setTheme</span>(<span class="str">'vivid'</span>)</div>
    <p>Build your own theme by overriding the CSS custom properties. See the <a href="#css-properties">CSS Properties</a> reference for the full list.</p>

    <h2 id="events">Events</h2>
    <p>Events are the only way user actions affect state. Drag events, click events, hover events — extensions intercept them, core processes them. Return <code>false</code> from any handler to cancel the action.</p>
    <div class="docs-code">chart.<span class="fn">on</span>(<span class="str">'onDragEnd'</span>, (row, update) =&gt; {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;console.<span class="fn">log</span>(\`\${row.name} moved to day \${update.start}\`)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">return false</span> <span class="cm">// cancel the update</span><br>})<br><br>chart.<span class="fn">on</span>(<span class="str">'onClick'</span>, (row, event) =&gt; {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;console.<span class="fn">log</span>(\`Clicked \${row.name}\`)<br>})</div>
    <h3>Event List</h3>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Event</th><th>Signature</th><th>Cancelable</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>onDragStart</td><td>(row, type: 'move' | 'resize-left' | 'resize-right' | 'progress') =&gt; void | false</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
        <tr><td>onDragMove</td><td>(row, delta: { days, progress? }) =&gt; void</td><td>No</td></tr>
        <tr><td>onDragEnd</td><td>(row, update: RowUpdate) =&gt; void | false</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
        <tr><td>onClick</td><td>(row, event: MouseEvent) =&gt; void</td><td>No</td></tr>
        <tr><td>onHover</td><td>(row | null) =&gt; void</td><td>No</td></tr>
        <tr><td>onCollapse</td><td>(row, collapsed: boolean) =&gt; void</td><td>No</td></tr>
        <tr><td>onViewChange</td><td>(view: string) =&gt; void</td><td>No</td></tr>
        <tr><td>onDensityChange</td><td>(density: string) =&gt; void</td><td>No</td></tr>
        <tr><td>onThemeChange</td><td>(theme: string) =&gt; void</td><td>No</td></tr>
        <tr><td>onRowUpdate</td><td>(row, changes: Partial&lt;Row&gt;) =&gt; void | false</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
        <tr><td>onRowReorder</td><td>(rowId, newIndex: number) =&gt; void</td><td>No</td></tr>
        <tr><td>onBeforeRender</td><td>(rows, state) =&gt; Row[]</td><td>No</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <!-- ═══ EXTENSIONS ═══ -->
    <h2 id="using-extensions">Using Extensions</h2>
    <p>Pass extensions in the config array. Registration order matters — later extensions override earlier ones for the same renderer key. Core registers first, then your extensions in array order.</p>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="kw">import</span> { todayMarker, tooltips, dependencyArrows } <span class="kw">from</span> <span class="str">'@emboss-js/core/extensions/free'</span><br><span class="kw">import</span> { sidebar, phases, milestones } <span class="kw">from</span> <span class="str">'@emboss-js/core/extensions/organize'</span><br><br><span class="kw">const</span> chart = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="fn">Emboss</span>(<span class="str">'#gantt'</span>, tasks, {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;extensions: [<span class="fn">todayMarker</span>, <span class="fn">tooltips</span>, <span class="fn">dependencyArrows</span>, <span class="fn">sidebar</span>, <span class="fn">phases</span>],<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;licenseKey: <span class="str">'EMB-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX'</span> <span class="cm">// required for paid extensions</span><br>})</div>
    <p>Free extensions work without a license key. Paid extensions (from the Organize bundle) require a key — without one, their code paths simply don't execute. No broken UI, no error states. The paid features are just absent.</p>

    <h2 id="today-marker">Today Marker</h2>
    <p>Free extension. Renders a pulsing indicator at today's position on the timeline. No configuration needed — just include it in your extensions array.</p>
    <ul class="docs-list">
      <li><strong>Line:</strong> 1.5px vertical line, <code>var(--emboss-today)</code> at 50% opacity, full chart height</li>
      <li><strong>Dot:</strong> 8px circle at the top of the line</li>
      <li><strong>Ring:</strong> 16px pulsing circle, scales 1&times; to 1.6&times; over 2 seconds</li>
      <li><strong>Glow:</strong> ~40px column at 4% opacity behind the line</li>
      <li><strong>Label:</strong> "TODAY" in monospace, 8px, above the dot</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="kw">import</span> { todayMarker } <span class="kw">from</span> <span class="str">'@emboss-js/core/extensions/free'</span><br><br><span class="kw">const</span> chart = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="fn">Emboss</span>(<span class="str">'#gantt'</span>, tasks, {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;extensions: [<span class="fn">todayMarker</span>]<br>})</div>

    <h2 id="tooltips">Tooltips</h2>
    <p>Free extension. Cursor-following cards that appear on hover, showing task name, dates, progress, and assignee. Boundary-aware positioning ensures they never clip off-screen.</p>
    <ul class="docs-list">
      <li>Dark card on light theme, light card on dark theme</li>
      <li>Shows task name, start/end dates, progress percentage</li>
      <li>Includes assignee when the data is present</li>
      <li>Smooth follow on cursor movement with slight offset</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="dependency-arrows">Dependency Arrows</h2>
    <p>Free extension. SVG arrows between dependent rows, rendered in an overlay above bars. <strong>Hidden by default</strong> — arrows appear when you hover a connected bar, then fade out when hover ends.</p>
    <h3>Routing</h3>
    <p>Start-to-start right-angle routing. Left edge of source to left edge of target. The path goes: horizontal left to a gutter column, vertical to target row, horizontal right into target start. Rounded joins at corners.</p>
    <h3>Status-Based Styling</h3>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>Line</th><th>Opacity</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Active</td><td>Solid 1.5px</td><td>0.65</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Future</td><td>Dashed (5 3)</td><td>0.5</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Completed</td><td>Solid 1.2px</td><td>0.4</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Connection dots (2.5px radius circles) appear at each endpoint, matching the path color and opacity.</p>

    <h2 id="writing-extensions">Writing Your Own Extension</h2>
    <p>Extensions are plain objects implementing the <code>EmbossExtension</code> interface. Declare what you provide — renderers, event handlers, row enrichment, CSS — and the core merges them in.</p>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="kw">const</span> myExtension: <span class="fn">EmbossExtension</span> = {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;name: <span class="str">'my-extension'</span>,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;type: <span class="str">'free'</span>,<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="cm">// Add a custom bar renderer for tasks</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;barRenderer: {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;task: (row, scale, state) =&gt; {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">const</span> el = document.<span class="fn">createElement</span>(<span class="str">'div'</span>)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;el.className = <span class="str">'my-custom-bar'</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;el.style.width = (row.duration * scale.dayWidth) + <span class="str">'px'</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">return</span> el<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;},<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="cm">// Enrich rows before render</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;enrichRows: (rows, state) =&gt; {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="kw">return</span> rows.<span class="fn">map</span>(r =&gt; ({<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;...r,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;isCritical: r.progress &lt; <span class="num">50</span> &amp;&amp; r.status === <span class="str">'active'</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}))<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;},<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="cm">// CSS injected into the document</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;styles: <span class="str">&#96;.my-custom-bar { background: red; }&#96;</span>,<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="cm">// Runs once when extension is registered</span><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;init: (emboss) =&gt; {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;emboss.<span class="fn">on</span>(<span class="str">'onClick'</span>, (row) =&gt; console.<span class="fn">log</span>(row.name))<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;}<br>}</div>
    <p>See the <a href="#extension-type">Extension Type</a> reference for the full interface.</p>

    <!-- ═══ ORGANIZE BUNDLE ═══ -->
    <h2 id="sidebar">Sidebar</h2>
    <span class="placeholder">Organize bundle</span>
    <p>Full-width or rail mode. The sidebar renders per-row cells synchronized with the timeline — row 5 in the sidebar is always row 5 on the chart.</p>
    <ul class="docs-list">
      <li><strong>Full mode:</strong> <code>var(--emboss-sidebar-w)</code> width (default 280px). Task names with status dots, phase pills with collapse chevrons, assignee avatars.</li>
      <li><strong>Rail mode:</strong> 48px. Phase pills (30&times;30px, phase color, centered letter). Task dots (8&times;8px).</li>
      <li><strong>Phase rows:</strong> Chevron (rotates on collapse) + colored pill + name + task count badge.</li>
      <li><strong>Task rows:</strong> Status dot + name + assignee avatar (if present).</li>
      <li><strong>Milestone rows:</strong> Diamond icon + italic name.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="kw">import</span> { sidebar } <span class="kw">from</span> <span class="str">'@emboss-js/core/extensions/organize'</span><br><br><span class="kw">const</span> chart = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="fn">Emboss</span>(<span class="str">'#gantt'</span>, tasks, {<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;extensions: [<span class="fn">sidebar</span>],<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;licenseKey: <span class="str">'EMB-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX'</span><br>})</div>

    <h2 id="phases">Phase Grouping</h2>
    <span class="placeholder">Organize bundle</span>
    <p>Collapsible groups that span their children. Color-coded thin bars (5px height) appear on the timeline spanning from earliest child start to latest child end. Click the chevron to expand or collapse.</p>
    <ul class="docs-list">
      <li>Phase progress is computed from children</li>
      <li>Phase color at 25% opacity on the timeline bar</li>
      <li>Sidebar shows colored pill + name + task count badge</li>
      <li>Collapsed phases hide all child rows</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="milestones">Milestones</h2>
    <span class="placeholder">Organize bundle</span>
    <p>Diamond markers for deadlines and checkpoints. 20&times;20px rotated square with 3px corner radius.</p>
    <ul class="docs-list">
      <li>2.5px border in phase color</li>
      <li>Background: <code>var(--emboss-surface)</code></li>
      <li>Progress fill bottom-to-top inside the diamond</li>
      <li>Glass highlight on top 50%</li>
      <li>Hover: scale 1.2&times;</li>
      <li>Done state: 45% opacity</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="inline-editing">Inline Editing</h2>
    <span class="placeholder">Organize bundle</span>
    <p>Click-to-edit on task and phase names directly in the sidebar. The input field gets a phase-colored border on focus. Enter to save, Escape to cancel. Changes flow through the <code>onRowUpdate</code> event, so you can intercept and validate before committing.</p>

    <!-- ═══ API REFERENCE ═══ -->
    <h2 id="emboss-class">Emboss Class</h2>
    <p>The main entry point. Constructor, instance methods, and event subscriptions.</p>
    <h3>Constructor</h3>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="kw">new</span> <span class="fn">Emboss</span>(selector: <span class="str">string</span>, rows: <span class="str">Row[]</span>, config?: <span class="str">EmbossConfig</span>)</div>
    <h3>Instance Methods</h3>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Signature</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>setView</td><td>(view: 'day' | 'week' | 'month' | 'quarter') =&gt; void</td><td>Change the time scale. Recalculates scale and re-renders.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>setDensity</td><td>(density: 'dense' | 'working' | 'presentation') =&gt; void</td><td>Change row spacing. Recalculates scale.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>setTheme</td><td>(theme: string) =&gt; void</td><td>Switch CSS theme by swapping the class on the root container.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>updateRow</td><td>(rowId: string, changes: Partial&lt;Row&gt;) =&gt; void</td><td>Merge partial changes into a row and re-render.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>toggleCollapse</td><td>(rowId: string) =&gt; void</td><td>Expand or collapse a row's children.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>addRow</td><td>(row: Row, afterId?: string) =&gt; void</td><td>Insert a new row. Placed after afterId, or at end.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>removeRow</td><td>(rowId: string) =&gt; void</td><td>Delete a row from the chart.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>on</td><td>(event: string, handler: Function) =&gt; void</td><td>Subscribe to an event.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>emit</td><td>(event: string, ...args: any[]) =&gt; void | false</td><td>Emit an event. Returns false if any handler cancels.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>use</td><td>(extension: EmbossExtension) =&gt; void</td><td>Register an extension at runtime.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>remove</td><td>(name: string) =&gt; void</td><td>Unregister an extension by name.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>render</td><td>() =&gt; void</td><td>Force a re-render of the chart.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>destroy</td><td>() =&gt; void</td><td>Unmount the chart and clean up event listeners.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="config">Configuration</h2>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>extensions</td><td>EmbossExtension[]</td><td>[]</td><td>Array of extensions to register.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>view</td><td>'day' | 'week' | 'month' | 'quarter'</td><td>'week'</td><td>Initial view mode.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>density</td><td>'working' | 'presentation' | 'dense'</td><td>'working'</td><td>Initial density. Presentation/dense require Organize license.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>theme</td><td>string</td><td>'grayscale'</td><td>Initial theme name.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>startDate</td><td>Date</td><td>new Date()</td><td>Project start date for day offset calculations.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>licenseKey</td><td>string</td><td>undefined</td><td>License key for paid extensions.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>moveDependencies</td><td>boolean</td><td>false</td><td>When dragging a row, also move its dependents.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>sidebar</td><td>{ columns?: string[] }</td><td>undefined</td><td>Sidebar configuration (requires Organize).</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="row-type">Row Type</h2>
    <p>The <code>Row</code> interface — the only data structure that flows through the system.</p>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>id</td><td>string</td><td>Unique identifier.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>type</td><td>'task' | 'phase' | 'milestone' | 'subtask'</td><td>Row type. Determines which renderer handles it.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>name</td><td>string</td><td>Display name.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>depth</td><td>number</td><td>Nesting level. 0 = top-level, 1 = under phase, 2 = subtask.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>parentId</td><td>string | null</td><td>ID of parent row (phase or task).</td></tr>
        <tr><td>collapsed</td><td>boolean</td><td>Whether children are hidden. Only meaningful for rows with children.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>hidden</td><td>boolean</td><td>True when a parent is collapsed. Renderer skips this row.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>start</td><td>number</td><td>Day offset from project start (0-indexed).</td></tr>
        <tr><td>duration</td><td>number</td><td>Length in days. 0 for milestones.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>progress</td><td>number</td><td>Completion percentage, 0–100.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>status</td><td>'done' | 'active' | 'upcoming'</td><td>Current status. Affects bar styling and opacity.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>dependencies</td><td>string[]</td><td>IDs of rows this row depends on.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3>Extension Fields (optional)</h3>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Added By</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>assignee</td><td>string</td><td>Team extension</td></tr>
        <tr><td>assigneeColor</td><td>string</td><td>Team extension</td></tr>
        <tr><td>phaseColor</td><td>string</td><td>Phases extension</td></tr>
        <tr><td>phaseName</td><td>string</td><td>Phases extension</td></tr>
        <tr><td>isCritical</td><td>boolean</td><td>Analyze extension</td></tr>
        <tr><td>children</td><td>string[]</td><td>Phases extension</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="scale-type">Scale Type</h2>
    <p>The <code>Scale</code> object controls pixel dimensions for the current view &times; density combination. Recalculated automatically when you call <code>setView()</code> or <code>setDensity()</code>.</p>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>dayWidth</td><td>number</td><td>Pixels per day. Ranges from 5 (dense/quarter) to 48 (presentation/day).</td></tr>
        <tr><td>rowHeight</td><td>number</td><td>Pixels per row. Ranges from 28 to 60.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>barHeight</td><td>number</td><td>Pixels for bar element. Ranges from 16 to 34.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>barRadius</td><td>number</td><td>Border-radius for bars. Half of barHeight.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>totalDays</td><td>number</td><td>Project span in days. Derived from data + padding.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>startDate</td><td>Date</td><td>First day of the project timeline.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>labelSize</td><td>number</td><td>Font size for bar labels, 9.5–13px.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="extension-type">Extension Type</h2>
    <p>The <code>EmbossExtension</code> interface. Everything an extension can provide.</p>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>name</td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Unique extension name.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>type</td><td>'free' | 'paid'</td><td>Yes</td><td>License tier. Paid extensions require a license key.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>bundle</td><td>string</td><td>No</td><td>Bundle name (e.g. 'organize'). Used for license checking.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>sidebarRenderer</td><td>Record&lt;string, SidebarRenderer&gt;</td><td>No</td><td>Sidebar renderers keyed by row type.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>barRenderer</td><td>Record&lt;string, BarRenderer&gt;</td><td>No</td><td>Timeline bar renderers keyed by row type.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>headerRenderer</td><td>HeaderRenderer</td><td>No</td><td>Custom timeline header renderer.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>handlers</td><td>Partial&lt;EmbossEvents&gt;</td><td>No</td><td>Event handlers to register.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>enrichRows</td><td>(rows, state) =&gt; Row[]</td><td>No</td><td>Transform rows before render (add computed fields).</td></tr>
        <tr><td>styles</td><td>string</td><td>No</td><td>CSS string injected into the document.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>init</td><td>(emboss: EmbossInstance) =&gt; void</td><td>No</td><td>Runs once when extension is registered.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3>Renderer Types</h3>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="kw">type</span> <span class="fn">SidebarRenderer</span> = (row: Row, state: EmbossState) =&gt; HTMLElement | <span class="kw">null</span><br><span class="kw">type</span> <span class="fn">BarRenderer</span>     = (row: Row, scale: Scale, state: EmbossState) =&gt; SVGElement | HTMLElement<br><span class="kw">type</span> <span class="fn">HeaderRenderer</span>  = (scale: Scale, state: EmbossState) =&gt; HTMLElement</div>

    <h2 id="css-properties">CSS Custom Properties</h2>
    <p>The complete list of <code>--emboss-</code> prefixed custom properties. Override these in your own CSS to create custom themes.</p>
    <h3>Surface &amp; Ink</h3>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Light</th><th>Dark</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>--emboss-bg</td><td>#f5f6f8</td><td>#0f1117</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-surface</td><td>#fff</td><td>#1a1d23</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-surface-2</td><td>#fafbfc</td><td>#1f222b</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-border</td><td>#f0f1f4</td><td>#2a2d36</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-ink</td><td>#1a1d23</td><td>#e5e7eb</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-ink-2</td><td>#374151</td><td>#d1d5db</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-ink-3</td><td>#6b7280</td><td>#9ca3af</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-ink-4</td><td>#9ca3af</td><td>#6b7280</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-ink-5</td><td>#d1d5db</td><td>#374151</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3>Bars &amp; Track</h3>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Light</th><th>Dark</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>--emboss-track</td><td>#e8ecf1</td><td>#2a2d36</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-track-radius</td><td colspan="2">13px</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-fill-active</td><td colspan="2">linear-gradient(90deg, #4b5563, #6b7280)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-fill-done</td><td colspan="2">linear-gradient(90deg, #9ca3af, #a3a3a3)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-fill-upcoming</td><td colspan="2">linear-gradient(90deg, #9ca3af, #a3a3a3)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-opacity-done</td><td colspan="2">0.45</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-opacity-upcoming</td><td colspan="2">0.5</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-today</td><td>#ef4444</td><td>#f87171</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3>Dimensions</h3>
    <table class="prop-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>--emboss-row-h</td><td>44px</td><td>Row height (overridden by density)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-bar-h</td><td>26px</td><td>Bar height (overridden by density)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-bar-r</td><td>13px</td><td>Bar border-radius</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-day-w</td><td>32px</td><td>Pixels per day (overridden by view)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-sidebar-w</td><td>280px</td><td>Sidebar width</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-label-size</td><td>11.5px</td><td>Label font size</td></tr>
        <tr><td>--emboss-grid-opacity</td><td>0.04</td><td>Grid line opacity</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3>Vivid Overrides</h3>
    <p>The Vivid theme (part of Organize bundle) replaces bar fills only:</p>
    <div class="docs-code"><span class="cm">/* Apply via .emboss-vivid class */</span><br>--emboss-fill-active:   linear-gradient(90deg, #3b82f6, #06b6d4);<br>--emboss-fill-done:     linear-gradient(90deg, #34d399, #06b6d4);<br>--emboss-fill-upcoming: linear-gradient(90deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);</div>
`;
---

